article.description: — Antonio Madlock's 16 points and seven rebounds helped Alabama State defeat Merrimack 66-60 in overtime on Saturday.
article.headline: Madlock's 16 lead Alabama State over Merrimack 66-60 in OT
article.linkText: Madlock's 16 lead Alabama State over Merrimack 66-60 in OT
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- — Antonio Madlock's 16 points and seven rebounds helped Alabama State defeat Merrimack 66-60 in overtime on Saturday. CJ Hines scored 14 points and Kendal Parker had 12 points for the Hornets (3-4). Adam Clark led the Warriors (3-4) in scoring, finishing with 12 points, four assists and two steals. Samba Diallo added 11 points and eight rebounds for Merrimack. Jordan Derkack finished with 11 points and four steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
